block content
  h2 Background / Foreground
  p This lesson should take you 30 minutes to complete. It will teach you about background vs foreground processes.

  h2 Video - 12 min
  p
    iframe(width="1120",height="630", src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/HzsgkzCL9ow", title="YouTube video player", frameborder="0", allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture", allowfullscreen)

  h2 Projects - 15 min
  ol
    li Open a file in vim and then send vim to the background with the ctrl z command.
    li Foreground the process you last sent to the background
    li List out all the jobs that you have running in the background
    li Start a process in the background immediately when it starts
    li What is the difference between ctl z and ctl c?

  h2 Nice Job!
  p You are now know the difference between background and foreground processes.
